  "text": "The present study demonstrated significantly high levels of IL-1β in serum of the COPD patients as compared to the healthy controls. A few studied previously undertaken have also reported a rise in IL-1β in COPD cases [CITATION_1] . It can thus be speculated that in COPD, IL-1β expression may be induced in monocytes due to increased IgE levels, which may lead to their increased release in blood, although we could not observe any correlation between both IL-1β and IgE due to the limited sample size.",
